From: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott@hotmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: airoha: Wait for RCU readers before PPE deinit

Readers access eth->npu under an RCU read-side critical section. After
removing the published pointer, wait for existing readers before deinitializing
and releasing the NPU object.

Signed-off-by: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott@hotmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
@@ -1659,6 +1659,7 @@ void airoha_ppe_deinit(struct airoha_eth
 	npu = rcu_replace_pointer(eth->npu, NULL,
 				  lockdep_is_held(&flow_offload_mutex));
 	if (npu) {
+		synchronize_rcu();
 		npu->ops.ppe_deinit(npu);
 		airoha_npu_put(npu);
 	}
